IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: We organize ourselves to establish and provide community resources, services and initiatives in support of people with mental, physical or sensory impairment, their families and those who provide support so that they may exercise responsibly their choice, preference and right, without limmitation, to a fully integrated life as citizens of pennsylvania.
IRS990.MissionDescription: We organize ourselves to establish and provide community resources, services and initiatives in support of people with mental, physical or sensory impairment, their families and those who provide support so that they may exercise responsibly their choice, preference and right, without limitation, to a fully integrated life as citizens of pennsylvania.
IRS990.Description: residential programs - Includes community living arrangements (CLA's), supported living and family supported living. The agency provides housing and programmatic support so that individuals can live an inclusive life within the community in the least restrictive setting possible so that they may pursue a quality life of independence.

Activity2.Description: children services: includes pre-school services, daycare, early intervention, head start programs and other educational initiatives for the preschooler. the agency provides programs on a daily basis to children below the age of six with disabilities and those without an inclusive environment. services include support to families, including counseling, and educational counseling, as well as preschool instruction, activities and a comprehensive lunch program including nutritional support for children.

Activity3.Description: Day and community support services: include the norcom community center, activities of daily living to both individuals living in cla's as well as their natural family setting and behavioral health interventions. services include an inclusive environment so that individuals over 21 years of age can continue to achieve new skills necessary for daily living; opportunities for volunteerism and service in order to develop social capital as well as behavioral health counseling, support and interventions for individuals with behavioral concerns.

ActivityOther.Description: vocational services: includes community integrated employment. the agency provides vocational counseling, skills development, job finding activities, placement and ongoing support so that individuals may be gainfully employed within community setting.
